Overview <p>Custom update loops allow fine-grained control over when and how systems execute.</p> Experience Level <p>Recommended: Intermediate Familiarity with <code>Update()</code> and basic profiling required.</p> What It Replaces <ul> <li>MonoBehaviour.Update  </li> <li>Overuse of Coroutines</li> </ul> Pros <ul> <li>Predictable execution</li> <li>Scales well with complexity</li> <li>Easier to debug</li> </ul> Sample Code <pre><code>public interface IUpdatable
{
    void Tick(float deltaTime);
}
</code></pre> Source Files <p>🔗 View on GitHub</p>
